The work done here is a collection of scripts written with help of Loco-Mujoco's own code and repository and dataset scheme to produce a simulation of a hip stability device for older adults

The device is intended for those with injury or disability/muscle weakness of 50-75 both male and female

The intent of the work here is to simulate a perturbation about the CoM at the toe off or initial contact stages of gait to represent improper weight shift

The goal from there is to produce a counter angular momentum to the body and help the leg to be repositioned inside the Margin of Stability to allow for a more stable body and easier recovery during the intial stages of a fall

The work is done with the framework of Loco-Mujoco, my understanding of the papers read and python and for body kinetics and kinematics along with system control
